name: Serials Directory (EBSCO)
description: The database includes bibliographic information as well as current pricing structures for popular serials. This resource contains: over 178,500 U.S. and international titles, including newspapers; historical data for an additional 20,000 titles; data from over 85,000 publishers worldwide, including e-mail and Internet addresses; Library of Congress and Dewey Decimal Classifications for every entry.
